            "is_major": false,
            "source": "GlobeNewswire",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "On February 18, 2025, Lead Real Estate Co., Ltd (Nasdaq: LRE), a Japanese luxury real estate developer operating in Tokyo, Kanagawa prefecture, and Sapporo, disclosed receiving a staff determination letter on February 12, 2025, from Nasdaq. The letter informed the Company of Nasdaq Staff's decision to delist LRE's securities from The Nasdaq Global Market due to non-compliance with Nasdaq Listing Rule 5450(b)(1)(C), which mandates a market value of publicly held shares at a minimum of $5,000,000. This action follows Nasdaq Listing Rule 5810(b) regulations.",
